== Code ==

{code}
class X { def unapply(v : Int) = Some(v + 1) }
val q = new X
5 match { case q(x) => x }
{code}

== What happened ==

{code}
java.lang.ClassCastException:  cannot be cast to 
{code}

== What expected ==

Prints 6. This works in the compiler, and works in the interpreter if I use an object rather than class + val.
